import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'])
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    state_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which state has the highest number of state capitals?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_lon = data['lon'].mean()
    avg_lat = data['lat'].mean()
    
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], label='State Capitals')
    plt.axvline(avg_lon, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Avg Longitude: {avg_lon:.2f}')
    plt.axhline(avg_lat, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'Avg Latitude: {avg_lat:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average longitude and latitude of state capitals?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    us_states = gpd.read_file('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json')
    capitals = gpd.GeoDataFrame(data, geometry=gpd.points_from_xy(data.lon, data.lat))
    capitals.crs = us_states.crs
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = us_states.boundary.plot(color='black', linewidth=1, figsize=(6, 6))
    capitals.plot(ax=ax, marker='o', color='red', markersize=5)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of state capitals by state?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
